Canidia. — o nec paternis, etc. : ‘unsullied by disgraceful parents‚’ implying that Canidia's parentage was dubious. With the phrase, cf. C. 2, 10, 6 obseleti sordes tecti, and Cic. pro Sest. 60 (virtus) neque alienis unquam sordibus obsolescit.

47 f. prudens anus: nor art thou a laag skilled to scatter‚ etc. The ashes of the poor whose relatives could not protect their tombs were stolen by such witches for their magio rites. —— novendialis : i.e. just put away. According to Apul. Met. 9⁷ 31 the funeral rites were not ended until the ninth day ( nono die completis apud tumulum sollemnibus).
